p.span: * Each CPU SW is built as a pre-linked static library

p.font: * Only a very small subset of symbols is exposed from this library. J
p.span: ust those used by natsim to start/stop/interrupt the embedded CPU execution.

p.font: * The embedded SW may be built with its own embedded C library. If not, the host C lib will be used.

p.span: * The native simulator "runner" is precompiled, and then linked with all CPUs SW to produce the final Linux executable.

div.p: * The executable is a plain Linux executable, which can be debugged and instrumented in the same ways as other Linux executables.
div.font: * The runner provides the overall entry point (main), and simulation scheduling, HW models, IRQ controller, as well as a basic CPU "simulation" (threading, and CPU start/sleep/interrupt simulation).
